<Layout title="Crowell Ch.1 — Conservation of Energy" favicon="⚛">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/physics/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to physics</a>

    <h1>Conservation of Energy</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Benjamin Crowell &middot; Simple Nature &middot; <a href="https://lightandmatter.com/area1sn.html">Ch. 1</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Energy is never created or destroyed. It converts between <strong>kinetic energy</strong> (motion) and <strong>potential energy</strong> (position). The <strong>work-energy theorem</strong> links force over distance to changes in kinetic energy. That is the entire chapter.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Kinetic Energy -->
    <h3>Kinetic energy</h3>
    <p>A mass m moving at speed v has kinetic energy KE = (1/2)mv&sup2;. Double the speed, quadruple the energy. This is why car crashes at highway speed are so much worse.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Ball at different heights with KE/PE bars -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
